<Author>alpha1145
<Content>Great Place to Stay I stayed there while on business in Phoenix. The area is really nice and there is a shopping center with a 30 screen movie theater nearby. There are many places to eat. The hotel was really nice and very clean. The breakfast offered was great with many choices (french toast, yogurt, bagels, juice, etc). Much better food than other places I've stayed. It was a little hard to find in the dark, so make sure you do your homework before you try and find it. The internet was a little on the slow side compared to my home comcast connection, but it worked for surfing pages. I would stay there again. I was there 3/26/07-3/29/07. 
