<Author>IllinoisTraveller
<Content>Nice place to stay We stayed at the Country Inn at the north end of Phoenix/Scottsdale. It's a clean, quiet place near shopping and the highway. It was a little difficult to find, even with the directions given. It faces an east/west freeway (I guess they call them that out there) on a one-way frontage road. Once we figured out it must be on the frontage road, we were fine. Breakfasts were decent. The room and beds were comfortable. I'd stay at this one again and will definitely give a try to other Country Inn  Suites hotels elsewhere. 
